       <h3>Bottle Hill Day 2014 </h3> 
       <p class="user-heading user-subheading" style="text-align: center;"><strong class="user-heading">Bottle Hill Day 2014 is </strong></p> 
       <p class="user-heading user-subheading" style="text-align: center;"><strong class="user-heading">Saturday, September 27th, 10am to 5pm!</strong></p> 
       <p>Bottle Hill Day is&nbsp;Madison's annual town festival and street fair, typically held on the first Saturday of October.&nbsp; It is a rain or shine event open to all and free of charge. &nbsp;Madison residents, businesses, and community organizations participate in this fun-filled day of food, entertainment, and shopping to raise money for the town.</p> 
       <p class="user-subheading"><strong class="user-heading"><em><a href="/uploads/45/bottle_hill_day_2014_application_packet.pdf">Click here</a>&nbsp;the 2014 Bottle Hill Day Application!</em></strong></p> 
       <p class="user-subheading"><strong class="user-heading"><em>Bottle Hill Day Vendors: Please</em> <a href="/uploads/45/food_vendors_madison_health_dept_.pdf">click here</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>for necessary information from the Health Department.</em></strong></p> 
       <p class="user-subheading">Interested in sponsoring the event? Please&nbsp;<a href="/uploads/45/2014_bhd_sponsorship_packet.pdf">click here</a>&nbsp;for information about our sponsorship opportunities!</p> 
       <p><img alt="BHD1" width="127" src="/photos/45/bhd_dr._bowen_live.jpg" height="101">&nbsp;<img alt="BHD2" width="127" src="/photos/45/bottlehilldayoctober7_2006_026.jpg" height="101">&nbsp;<img alt="BHD3" width="127" src="/photos/45/photo_010.jpg" height="102">&nbsp;<img alt="BHD4" width="139" src="/photos/45/cimg0096.jpg" height="101"><br><br><strong>Events include:</strong></p> 
       <p>* Live music...<em>from local bands and the Original Music School</em><br>* Rock climbing...<em>free at Blue Ridge Mountain Sports</em><br>* Auto show...<em>featuring assorted cars and offering awards &amp; door prizes</em><br>* Food court...<em>with tasty samplings from Madison's best eateries</em><br>* Family activities...<em>Family Fun Zone with rides and inflatables</em><br>... and MORE!<br><br><img alt="BHD5" width="152" src="/photos/45/12.jpg" height="101"><img alt="BHD7" width="137" src="/photos/45/photo_019.jpg" height="100">&nbsp;<img alt="BHD8" width="104" src="/photos/45/cimg0137.jpg" height="101">&nbsp;<img alt="BHD9" width="144" src="/photos/45/cimg0126.jpg" height="100"></p> 
       <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt="" width="227" src="/photos/45/bhd_2012_left.jpg" height="400">&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt="" width="235" src="/photos/45/bhd_2012_right.jpg" height="400"></p> 
       <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img alt="" width="400" src="/photos/45/bhd12map.jpg" height="346"></p> 
       <p>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<strong class="user-heading"><br></strong><strong class="user-heading"><br>Bottle Hill Day 2013 was a HUGE success!</strong></p> 
       <table> 
        <tbody>
         <tr> 
          <td> <p><strong>Bottle Hill Day is organized by the Downtown Development Commission, the same volunteers who bring you...</strong></p> 
           <ul> 
            <li><strong>May Day</strong></li> 
            <li><strong>Farmers Market</strong></li> 
            <li><strong>Taste of Madison</strong></li> 
            <li><strong>University Town Tour</strong></li> 
            <li><strong>New Parking Signs</strong></li> 
            <li><strong>Window Contests</strong></li> 
           </ul> </td> 
          <td> <p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p> </td> 
         </tr> 
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <p class="user-heading">If you have questions or need additional information, please call the Bottle Hill Day Hotline at 973-937-8084.</p> 
